Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as exclusive marketing agent, is pleased to offer 12A, 14 & 16 Shinfield Avenue, St Ives. Located in one of Sydney's most idyllic settings, this rare, landmark development is not an opportunity often offered to the open market.

The property will be made available for sale by Expressions of Interest closing Thursday, 15 September at 4:00PM (AEST). 12A, 14 & 16 Shinfield Avenue, St Ives represents a top tier residential development opportunity, capitalising on the following key attributes:

- DA approval for 51 apartments, comprising a generous mix of 10 x 1 Bedroom, 36 x 2 Bedroom and 5 x 3 Bedroom

- Secure basement parking for 73 cars

- Vast 3,010 sqm* consolidated land parcel

- Paramount location - situated minutes from the St Ives Shopping Village

- Outstanding and well-connected residential setting in Sydney's esteemed Upper North Shore


For more information, please contact the selling agents.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: DA APPROVED NORTH SHORE DEVELOPMENT SITE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to present 36 Killeaton Street, St Ives. The property is an outstanding opportunity to acquire a DA approved development site for a childcare centre in a suburb with a leading family demographic.

36 Killeaton Street, St Ives benefits from the following key attributes:

- Approved 90 place childcare centre with 23 car spaces
- Heads of Agreement signed for 15 year lease to an established childcare operator 
- Agreed net rent: $482,356 per annum^ + GST
- Large 1,634sqm^ site
- Family friendly neighborhood with numerous primary and secondary schools
- Affluent suburb with growing catchment 
- Prime location within walking distance to St Ives Shopping Village

The property will be offered for sale via Expressions of Interest closing on Wednesday 20 September 2017 at 4:30pm AEST.

For further details, please contact the exclusive CBRE selling agents.

^Approximate

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: BUILDERS’ DELIGHT’ – DA APPROVED AND CC IMMINENT TOWNHOUSE DEVELOPMENT SITE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
47 Kitchener Street, St Ives offers purchasers a unique development opportunity in Sydney's esteemed Upper North Shore.

Situated on a vast 4,668 sqm*, the property provides opportunity to subdivide three large lots (1,500sqm each) and an enviable address for the construction of low density residential housing. Well positioned in the woodland serenity of St Ives, and yet only 20KM* from the Sydney CBD, the site offers the perfect combination of residential escape and metropolitan connectivity. With the Sydney housing market in the midst of burgeoning growth, 47 Kitchener Street, St Ives is a truly rare chance to secure a property with such a special land size offering
• Land area of 4,668sqm
• Three large lot subdivision - 1,500sqm* each(STCA)
• Low density residential development (STCA)
• Dual street access
• Very rare offering in the market

This premier small land subdivision opportunity is for sale via an Expression of Interest campaign.

All Expressions of Interest are to be submitted in writing to CBRE by 6th April 2016 at 3pm (AEST)
